#: ../../B/bigot.rst:5
msgid "bigot"
msgstr "bigot"

#: ../../B/bigot.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/bigot.rst:9
msgid ""
"[common] A person who is religiously attached to a particular computer, "
"language, operating system, editor, or other tool (see :ref:`religious-"
"issues`\\). Usually found with a specifier; thus, Cray bigot, ITS bigot, APL"
" bigot, VMS bigot, Berkeley bigot. Real bigots can be distinguished from "
"mere partisans or zealots by the fact that they refuse to learn alternatives"
" even when the march of time and/or technology is threatening to obsolete "
"the favored tool. It is truly said \"You can tell a bigot, but you can't "
"tell him much.\" Compare :ref:`weenie`\\, :ref:`Amiga-Persecution-"
"Complex`\\."
msgstr ""
"[一般的]特定のコンピューター・言語・オペレーティングシステム・エディタ、その他のツールに宗教的なまでに固執する人(\\ "
":ref:`religious-issues`\\ を参照)。たいてい修飾語を伴う。すなわち、Cray bigot、ITS bigot、APL "
"bigot、VMS bigot、Berkeley "
"bigot。本物のbigotは、単なる党派人や熱狂者とは、時間および/または技術の進歩がお気に入りのツールを陳腐化させようとしているときでさえ代替手段を学ぼうとしない、という点で区別できる。「bigotは見分けられるが、bigotに言い聞かせることはほとんどできない(You"
" can tell a bigot, but you can't tell him much)」とはよく言ったものだ。\\ "
":ref:`weenie`\\ 、\\ :ref:`Amiga-Persecution-Complex`\\ と比較せよ。"
